Use a null-prototype object or sanitize keys:

```javascript
// Create object without prototype
const safe = Object.create(null);
Object.assign(safe, sanitizedInput);

// Or filter dangerous keys
const sanitize = (obj) => {
const clean = {};
for (const key of Object.keys(obj)) {
if (key !== '__proto__' && key !== 'constructor') {
clean[key] = obj[key];
}
}
return clean;
};
```

